data.description: Rare opportunity to own this Executive Home in highly sought after Whitcomb Place!  Sitting high and dry in Flood Zone X, this beautiful home checks all the boxes on your must have list.  Features include:  Ceramic Tile throughout the entire home, Plantation Shutters, built-in Custom Designed Closets in all the bedrooms, Custom Kitchen, 1 year old Custom Sliding Glass Doors and Windows, 2.5 year old roof, and 5 year old screened pool enclosure. The Primary Bedroom is its own private sanctuary, located just off the foyer to the left, and has his and her closets, is en-suite with dual vanities, garden tub, separate glass shower stall, private water closet, and sliders to easily access the pool deck and outdoor kitchen.  As you leave the Primary Bedroom, you enter the Living Room, which is currently utilized as a bar area, and has sliding glass doors to the pool deck. Continuing on, you will see the Formal Dining area, complete with a stunning Chandelier, acquired in Historic New Orleans.  When you get to the kitchen, you will be delighted by the beautiful Granite Countertops, the French Provincial Cabinets with soft close drawers, a Custom Pantry with ample storage, the large island with additional storage, Stainless Steel Appliances, and gorgeous pendant lights.  The Family Room is open to the Kitchen, so you can prepare that feast and still be part of the crowd.  Picture yourself curled up by the  Fireplace on a chilly winter evening, enjoying a good book or just relaxing.  Beyond the Family Room, you will find the Laundry Room, complete with laundry sink and cabinets.  The 2nd bath is next, with a shower/tub combo, dual sinks with Granite Counter tops, and access to the pool deck.  The 3 additional bedrooms all have ceiling fans and built in closets.  The pool area has an Outdoor Kitchen, plenty of lounging space, in ground spa, and of course that lovely pool to cool off on our hot summer days.  The garage has space for 3 vehicles, and is 660 square feet!  Close to Historic Downtown Tarpon Springs, The Sponge Docks, Fred Howard Park, Sunset Beach, and only a block from Whitcomb Bayou!  This extraordinary home will not last long, so book your appointment today!
